                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>James</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Reginald</forename> de <surname>Morton</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
               grants to <persName nymRef="Morton">
                           <forename>Michael</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Morton</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, the
               whole of his part which lie has in '<placeName type="minor">le Polsiche</placeName>' 
               to make a fish-pond, with the whole
               reflow of water and sufficient land for the same, for which the said Michael gives
               the whole of his part which he has in a certain meadow called 
               '<placeName type="minor">le Hokmedue</placeName>,' near the
               water-mill of <placeName key="place_108521">Morton</placeName>, and half a mark.
               (<origDate when="1260">1260</origDate>.)
               Witn. <persName>sir <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Cavershwalle</surname>, sheriff of <placeName type="county" role="sheriff" key="place_000069">Staffordshire</placeName> and <placeName role="sheriff" type="county" key="place_000067">Salop</placeName>
                        </persName>, etc.
               . </p>
